      <h3>Common Reasons for Removal</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Inadequate weight loss:</strong> Only achieving 20-30% excess weight loss</li>
        <li><strong>Band slippage:</strong> Band moves out of position (15-20% of patients)</li>
        <li><strong>Band erosion:</strong> Band erodes through stomach wall (1-3% of patients)</li>
        <li><strong>Port complications:</strong> Infection, leakage, or tubing issues</li>
        <li><strong>Chronic vomiting:</strong> Band too tight, causing severe reflux/vomiting</li>
        <li><strong>Esophageal dilation:</strong> Esophagus stretches due to band obstruction</li>
        <li><strong>Patient request:</strong> Dissatisfaction with results or lifestyle restrictions</li>
